=<center>'''''Phenomenon 5'''''</center>=

<div id="talebox">
I was rummaging through a supply crate in [[Level 1]]. To my shock, a GoPro was sitting at the bottom corner of the crate, hidden underneath a layer of hay. Granted, its battery was running low, the screen was glitching a bit and some parts were flimsily chipped off, but it could still be used. I decided that I would only use it for special moments, like finding those fabled "safe havens" for the first time.

After a few days of staying here, I decided to embark on a new journey, as constant parking garages and hallways drove me to boredom. I went from [[Level 2|one dangerous level]], [[Level 660|and another]], [[Level 23|and yet another]], and so on. I've had several close encounters through my journey. Luckily, I encountered [[Level_98#The_Diner_Group|a colony]] in my journey, they were hospitable people and I felt comfortable with them. I talked to them for a while and then I asked them about safe havens. Most of them said that I'd live five lifetimes before I encounter one.

I decided that due to the relative safeness of the level I was staying in, and the cordiality of this community, I decided that I might stay here for a long time. I took out my GoPro, and took a group selfie with three others in the group. After that I decided to explore the level a bit more, since I was too busy meddling with the colony.

I unsuspectingly entered a regular dining room, when suddenly, a white blob-like void rushed in from the windows and went straight at me, and a second later my whole vision was whited out, as if I was in [[the Whole]]. I could still move and feel my surroundings, but I was blinded. It still affected me even when I closed my eyes. I was utterly horrified, and I screamed at the top of my lungs, moving in erratic directions trying to somehow get it off me. I was so far away from the colony that my cries for help were muffled into a hardly audible wisp.

</div>
