<div id="headingbox">Description</div>
<div class="complex-description">
Phenomenon 5, '''Camera's Obscurity''', manifests to wanderers taking photographs within the Backrooms as a blindingly white blob obscuring their vision. It occurs once a wanderer takes a picture with any camera. After one to three minutes, the blob appears from the farthest point the photographer is viewing, zooming into their position and filling up their entire vision after one second. The wanderer's vision is then whited out, even with closed eyes. After a minute, the wanderer's vision abruptly returns to normal.

If the photographer moves their body erratically, especially their head, and constantly blinking their eyes, the blob may disappear quicker. However, doing this may result in various injuries, primarily concussions. '''Camera's Obscurity''' is invisible to bystanders and is only visible to the photographer. Other body senses remain intact while the blob blinds the photographer, although one may hear static-like noise and smell a faint, electrical scent during the event.

'''Camera's Obscurity''' has an approximate 80% manifestation rate. Oddly, it is mitigable when using a device with an attached camera rather than a dedicated camera, with a halved manifestation rate. Additionally, the blob will not appear if the wanderer leaves the level where they took the photo before the manifestation. The phenomenon affects not only humans but also Partial and False [[Entity 9|Facelings]], [[Counter Entities|Counter-Entities]], [[Glowfolk]], and more<ref>If the entity is capable of vision and can operate a camera, they are susceptible to Camera's Obscurity.</ref>.

Sometimes, a '''Mini Obscurity''' may form. It is when the photographer's vision whites out, yet they still see vague outlines of their surroundings. It happens if the photo taken is of low quality or slightly corrupted, or the wanderer is in a specific Backrooms level where '''Camera's Obscurity''' is not as effective<ref>These specific levels include [[Level 330]], [[Level 399]], [[Level 699]], [[Level 37]], [[Level 100]], [[Level 154]], [[Level 48]], [[Level 280]], [[Level 833]], [[Level 798]], and [[Level 88]]. Any sublevels of the mentioned levels are also included.</ref>.<!--NOTE: if you think this phenomenon is lore breaking to some levels, just add that level to this long list--> A '''Mini Obscurity''' manifests faster than its counterpart, at thirty seconds to one minute, and can last up to two minutes. Performing erratic movements also cannot mellow out the phenomenon, although a photographer's instincts will not incentivize them to do so.

<div class="article-subheading">History</div>
The first instances of '''Camera's Obscurity''' appeared in the early 1940s when photography first became widespread in the Backrooms. However, some believe it dates back further due to camera technology dating back over a century. It was a rare phenomenon, with an estimated manifestation rate of 1-2% until February 2002, when its prevalence boosted to modern rates in one month. Strangely, during this month, rumors of a supposed "[[Entity 1|cameraman]]" spread rapidly amongst wanderers; some theorize that the two are related, although this claim remains unproven.

